00:15:44.530 --> 00:15:48.960
and my research on to the
images of the planet earth

00:15:48.960 --> 00:15:51.550
and children's book
theory before that.

00:15:51.550 --> 00:15:54.760
In the book -- how picture
books work Maria Nikolajeva

00:15:54.760 --> 00:15:59.030
and Carol Scott assert that and
I quote, the unique character

00:15:59.030 --> 00:16:02.510
of picture books is based on
the combination of two levels

00:16:02.510 --> 00:16:05.780
of communication, the
visual and the verbal.

00:16:05.780 --> 00:16:09.400
They continue on by stating
that if we are making use

00:16:09.400 --> 00:16:13.590
of semiotic terminology, we can
say that picture books communicate

00:16:13.590 --> 00:16:16.620
by means of two separate
sets of signs,

00:16:16.620 --> 00:16:19.070
the iconic and the conventional.

00:16:19.070 --> 00:16:23.310
Iconic or representational signs
are those in which the signifier

00:16:23.310 --> 00:16:26.620
and the signified are
related by common qualities.

00:16:26.620 --> 00:16:30.950
That is where the sign is a direct
representation of the signified.

00:16:30.950 --> 00:16:34.630
A picture of a printer on a
computer's command menu is an icon,

00:16:34.630 --> 00:16:37.120
a direct representation
of the printer.

00:16:37.120 --> 00:16:39.780
In most cases we do not
need special knowledge

00:16:39.780 --> 00:16:42.800
to understand a simple icon.

00:16:43.840 --> 00:16:47.000
Conventional signs have
no direct relationship

00:16:47.000 --> 00:16:48.660
with the object signified.

00:16:48.660 --> 00:16:51.900
The word print in a menu
only conveys the meaning

00:16:51.900 --> 00:16:56.040 position:56%
if you process the code, that is you
must know what letters stand for.

00:16:56.040 --> 00:16:57.830
But letters together
to produce words

00:16:57.830 --> 00:17:00.070
and understand what
the word stands for.

00:17:00.070 --> 00:17:03.310
Conventional signs are based on
an agreement among the [inaudible]

00:17:03.310 --> 00:17:07.050
of a particular language, both the
spoken language and communication,

00:17:07.050 --> 00:17:09.830
such as gestures, dress
code and emblems.

00:17:09.830 --> 00:17:13.330
For anyone outside the given
community conventional signs do not

00:17:13.330 --> 00:17:17.900
carry any meaning or at best,
the meaning is ambivalent.

00:17:17.900 --> 00:17:22.960
Thus, to understand the word
printer [inaudible] or I'm going

00:17:22.960 --> 00:17:27.040
to mangle the Finish
kirjoitin, you need to be fluent

00:17:27.040 --> 00:17:28.450
in the language in question.

00:17:28.450 --> 00:17:31.880
Whereas, the icon that symbolizes
the printer transcends one specific

00:17:31.880 --> 00:17:36.240
language and should hopefully allow
you to print things on computers

00:17:36.240 --> 00:17:39.190
where the language is set to
one that you do not speak.

00:17:39.190 --> 00:17:41.680
And if you've ever
accidentally changed the language

00:17:41.680 --> 00:17:43.250
of your operating system into one

00:17:43.250 --> 00:17:46.900
that you do not speak you notice
how long it takes to get back

00:17:46.900 --> 00:17:48.470
to something you're familiar with.

00:17:48.470 --> 00:17:54.210
So the printer hopefully should
work even if it's set to Chinese.

00:17:54.210 --> 00:17:57.260
Both Nikolajeva and Scott
call conventional signs

00:17:57.260 --> 00:18:00.900
and iconic signs have existed
in human culture for a long time

00:18:00.900 --> 00:18:04.560
and have not only given rise to two
parallel types of communication,

00:18:04.560 --> 00:18:08.240 position:56%
visual and verbal, but also have
been frequently put into interaction

00:18:08.240 --> 00:18:12.340
with each other in such multimedia
forms as say the theater, movies,

00:18:12.340 --> 00:18:17.710
TV shows, video games, comic books
and of course also picture books.

00:18:17.710 --> 00:18:21.450
Both the images and the words used
in picture books are complex signs.

00:18:21.450 --> 00:18:24.770
The function of the words
are the conventional signs.

00:18:24.770 --> 00:18:27.750
To stay with Nikolajeva
and Scott's terminology is

00:18:27.750 --> 00:18:30.700
to narrate, to retell, to report.

00:18:30.700 --> 00:18:34.010
Whereas, the images are there
to describe, to represent,

00:18:34.010 --> 00:18:37.710
to illustrate, to visualize what
has been narrated to offer more

00:18:37.710 --> 00:18:40.330
or less concrete representation
of the more

00:18:40.330 --> 00:18:43.430
or less abstract concept
being narrated.

00:18:43.430 --> 00:18:47.660
And picture books exists
somewhere between the two polls

00:18:47.660 --> 00:18:49.430
of word and picture interaction.

00:18:49.430 --> 00:18:52.330
On the one poll you find
text without pictures

00:18:52.330 --> 00:18:56.490
and on the other poll you
find pictures without text.

00:18:56.490 --> 00:18:59.040
So somewhere in between
you find the picture book.

00:18:59.040 --> 00:19:02.190
Are there lots of pictures and very
little words or are there a lot

00:19:02.190 --> 00:19:06.620
of words and very few pictures,
it's all a give-and-take.

00:19:06.620 --> 00:19:11.700 position:56%
And even there differentiations they
need to be made between narrative

00:19:11.700 --> 00:19:14.810
and non-narrative interactions
of the two extremes.

00:19:14.810 --> 00:19:18.050
So is it a story or
is it a dictionary.

00:19:18.050 --> 00:19:21.210
Is it a picture narrative or
is it a picture dictionary,

00:19:21.210 --> 00:19:24.620
like A is for apple
and B is for beer,

00:19:24.620 --> 00:19:29.410
well probably not in
a children's book.

00:19:29.410 --> 00:19:32.760
According to Nikolajeva and Scott,
images and text can interact

00:19:32.760 --> 00:19:36.360 position:56%
in a number of different ways from
being symmetrical where the pictures

00:19:36.360 --> 00:19:40.490 position:56%
and the text tell two mutually
redundant narratives all the way via

00:19:40.490 --> 00:19:43.030
a number of steps to
selective picture books

00:19:43.030 --> 00:19:46.080
where two narratives are told
independently of one another

00:19:46.080 --> 00:19:50.460
and can, therefore, also
contradict each other.

00:19:50.460 --> 00:19:54.230
The theory, however, concerns
itself with narrative picture books

00:19:54.230 --> 00:19:57.830
that tell fictional stories
and does not focus so much

00:19:57.830 --> 00:20:02.210
on nonfictional narrative books nor
did any other scholars that have

00:20:02.210 --> 00:20:04.760
so far found focus on those books.

00:20:04.760 --> 00:20:07.680
So most of these intricately
interwoven narratives

00:20:07.680 --> 00:20:09.110
that Nikolajeva and Scott write

00:20:09.110 --> 00:20:12.980
about are not actually
present in what I am finding.

00:20:12.980 --> 00:20:15.340
In a large amount of the
books that I have been looking

00:20:15.340 --> 00:20:18.910
at are what they kind of
lump together as plate books,

00:20:18.910 --> 00:20:22.190
meaning nonfiction
illustrated books.

00:20:22.190 --> 00:20:25.150
I will show you that
notwithstanding the lack

00:20:25.150 --> 00:20:28.630
of theoretical in-depth
analysis so far.

00:20:28.630 --> 00:20:31.230
Depending on the time these
books were published and the age

00:20:31.230 --> 00:20:35.180
of the intended reader the variety
and the interplay between the text

00:20:35.180 --> 00:20:37.880
and the illustration
nevertheless takes place.

00:20:37.880 --> 00:20:40.210
One of my goals for my
own book project is also

00:20:40.210 --> 00:20:44.090
to formulate a comprehensive theory
of the interaction between images

00:20:44.090 --> 00:20:47.330
and text in nonfiction
narrative children's books based

00:20:47.330 --> 00:20:51.630
on existing scholarly
work of course.

00:20:51.630 --> 00:20:52.960
So that's one thing
we're looking at.

00:20:52.960 --> 00:20:55.710
And the second thing that really
interested me in my project

00:20:55.710 --> 00:20:59.060
and that I want to introduce
you to for like the next two

00:20:59.060 --> 00:21:02.750
or three minutes is the interaction
between metaphors and similes

00:21:02.750 --> 00:21:07.280
when talking about the planet
earth and children's books.

00:21:07.280 --> 00:21:12.970
So earth is like a ball
or earth is a ball,

00:21:12.970 --> 00:21:15.120
those are the two things
I'm finding.

00:21:15.120 --> 00:21:20.490
So a simile earth is like a
ball is a figure of speech

00:21:20.490 --> 00:21:23.910
that involves the comparison
of one thing to another thing

00:21:23.910 --> 00:21:26.890
of a different kind used
to make a description

00:21:26.890 --> 00:21:29.860
that is then more emphatic
or more vivid.

00:21:29.860 --> 00:21:34.290
The metaphor earth is a ball is a
figure of speech in which a word

00:21:34.290 --> 00:21:38.220
or phrase literally denoting one
kind of object or idea is used

00:21:38.220 --> 00:21:43.380 position:56%
in place of another to suggest a
likeness or an analogy between them.

00:21:43.380 --> 00:21:48.750
While a simile compares two items,
a metaphor directly equates them.

00:21:48.750 --> 00:21:51.180
In his book the Philosophy
of Frederick I.

00:21:51.180 --> 00:21:55.300
A. Richards describes metaphors
as and this is another quotation,

00:21:55.300 --> 00:21:57.500 position:56%
the supreme agent by which disparate

00:21:57.500 --> 00:22:00.670
and hitherto unconnected
things are brought together.

00:22:00.670 --> 00:22:04.870
And he also calls metaphors a
transaction between contexts.

00:22:04.870 --> 00:22:07.390
What a metaphor does
is not just to compare,

00:22:07.390 --> 00:22:11.200
but to merge two distinct
contexts together.

00:22:11.200 --> 00:22:14.970
As my talk is called images of the
Earth in American Children's Book

00:22:14.970 --> 00:22:16.730
and not metaphors regarding
the Earth

00:22:16.730 --> 00:22:19.660
in American Children's Books
we're going to be focusing more

00:22:19.660 --> 00:22:22.630
on visual representations
rather than verbal ones

00:22:22.630 --> 00:22:24.570
and the interplay between the two.

00:22:24.570 --> 00:22:28.080
But in my final project I will
definitely be looking at both

00:22:28.080 --> 00:22:31.930
and we're going to touch on
